As New Year’s resolutions fall by the wayside, sometimes technology is needed to keep people from dipping their hand in the cookie jar.

And one British start-up thinks Sammy Screamer could help.

Sammy Screamer is a ‘cute little movement sensor’ that can be attached to objects, such as a cookie jar and beeps at people who try to move or open them – as well as alerting the owner to the invasion.

