The triangular movement sensor has a shocked facial expression and will be controlled by a smartphone app when it is launched in August.

It is designed as a device for parents, but will be able to be used by anyone to keep an eye on any object – including fridges and jars to keep dieters on the straight and narrow.

The person in control of Sammy Screamer will be able to choose how loud they want her to beep and how sensitive to movement they want her to be, by using a free smartphone app.

