They will then be able to attach her to the object they want to guard - from a fridge to a bag, or a room that is out of bounds - using the device’s concealed magnet or cord to attach it.

The sensor has a Bluetooth unit, accelerometer, a battery and speaker inside.

When the device is moved it will beep and will send a push notification to its owner’s smartphone.

Tom Evans, founder of Bleep Bleeps, the company behind Sammy Screamer, said the device can be used to keep bags safe, or can be fixed to a pushchair or bike to let people know if it is moved.

